      "role": "user",
      "content": "i get that there are two sides, but isn't there a bit more to it than just \"differing beliefs\"? like, if we look at the actual outcomes in different countries, doesn't the data usually show that universal systems are more effective at providing care for everyone? so isn't the \"inefficiency\" argument kind of just a way to protect private profits?",
