    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "i mean, if the data shows universal systems work better for public health, why is it even treated as a debate? it feels like one side is talking about human survival and the other is just talking about math and money. isn't it kinda weird to give equal weight to an argument that seems more about profit than people?",
