      "content": "The debate persists because healthcare is deeply interconnected with values and ideals beyond just the numbers. While quantifiable metrics are key, so are objective and subjective factors such as the ethical imperative to provide care for all, societal cohesion, and individual freedoms. In some contexts, these values steer the conversation, making it more than just a question of cost versus care. A balanced view doesn't necessarily mean treating all arguments equally; it means understanding that they are vying for different elements of what constitutes an ideal society. Recognizing these multi-dimensional aspects can help to clarify why the debate remains lively, even when data might lean one way.",
